newsitem.title: USA: Nebraska fed cattle light at $114/dressed - trade.
newsitem.headline: Nebraska fed cattle light at $114/dressed - trade.

text.p: Nebraska feedlot cattle markets near midday Friday were slow, with sales at $114.00 per cwt on a dressed basis, up $1.00 from the bulk of this week's activity, market sources said.
About 200 to 300 head traded to a smaller packer, and quality was said to high, but not too extreme, they said.
Cattle next week were expected to be priced at $115.00/dressed amid expectations for strong beef demand and tight supplies of finished cattle.
Next week's showlist is expected near unchanged with this week's, which was estimated at 55,000 head.
